.TH STEGOFORGE 1 "2026-07-05" "v1.3.4" "CTF Toolkit"
.SH NAME
stegoforge \- automated steganography & forensics toolkit for CTF challenges
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B stegoforge
[OPTIONS]
.I <file|directory>
.SH DESCRIPTION
StegoForge runs multiple analysis modules on the target file to detect hidden
data, extract embedded content, and identify CTF flags. When a flag is found,
analysis stops immediately and the flag is printed.

.SH OUTPUT MODES
.TP
.B normal (default)
Only the final flag or "No flag found" is printed.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Show module headers and findings (keywords, flags, decoded data) during
analysis. Each finding is prefixed with a
.RB \(bu
symbol.
.TP
.B \-vv, \-\-vv
Show every external command executed by the analysis modules. Commands are
numbered sequentially. Useful for understanding exactly what the tool does.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Print results as a JSON object with file, flags, count, and output fields.
.TP
.B \-\-summary
Print a one-line summary per file in the format:
.RS
file.png \(rarr Flag: picoCTF{...}
.RE

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Show module progress, findings, and results during analysis.
.TP
.B \-vv, \-\-vv
Show external tool commands as they are executed.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-recursive
If the target is a directory, scan all files recursively.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output \fIdir\fR
Specify output directory (default: output/sessions/PID).
.TP
.B \-w, \-\-wordlist \fIfile\fR
Password list for brute-force attacks (steghide, zip, fcrackzip).
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-list
List all available modules with priority, supported file types, and
what they produce.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Print results as JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-summary
Print compact one-line summary.
.TP
.B \-\-readonly
Work on a temporary copy. Original file is not modified.
.TP
.B \-\-docker
Force execution inside a Docker container. Automatically falls back to
Docker if native tools are missing.
.TP
.B \-\-doctor
Check whether all required dependencies are installed.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show brief help and exit.

.SH MODULE SYSTEM
StegoForge uses a priority-based module system. Each module:
.IP \(bu 3
targets specific file types (e.g. png, jpg, *, txt)
.IP \(bu 3
produces typed findings (keyword, flag, base64_string, reconstructed, etc.)
.IP \(bu 3
can be triggered by findings from other modules via the pipeline system

Use
.B \-l
to list all modules with their priority, types, and products.

.SH RECURSIVE ANALYSIS
When the target is a directory and
.B \-r
is given, all files in the directory are analyzed. Files extracted by
binwalk, foremost, or other carving tools are automatically re-analyzed
up to 2 levels deep.

.SH REPAIR
Corrupted files (truncated headers, CRC mismatches) are detected and
automatically repaired when possible. Repaired files are saved to
.IR output/sessions/PID/repaired/
and re-analyzed.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B stegoforge image.png
Analyze image.png, print the flag.
.TP
.B stegoforge \-v image.jpg
Analyze with module progress visible.
.TP
.B stegoforge \-vv image.png
Analyze and show every command being executed.
.TP
.B stegoforge \-\-json \-r ~/challenges/
Recursively scan a directory, output JSON.
.TP
.B stegoforge \-w rockyou.txt image.jpg
Use a wordlist for steghide password cracking.
.TP
.B stegoforge \-\-readonly corrupted.bin
Analyze without modifying the original file.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I output/sessions/PID/
Default output directory.
.TP
.I output/sessions/PID/carved/
Extracted and carved files (foremost, binwalk, dd).
.TP
.I output/sessions/PID/repaired/
Repaired versions of corrupted files.
.TP
.I output/sessions/PID/pipeline/
Intermediate data for pipeline-triggered modules.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B STEGOFORGE_TEST
If set to 1, pipeline processing and recursive extraction are disabled
(used by the test suite).

.SH BUGS
Report issues at https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/issues
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR strings (1),
.BR zsteg (1),
.BR exiftool (1),
